JOHANNESBURG, March 14 – Two 15-year-old suspects believed to be involved in the murder of a Mondeor High School learner were arrested on Thursday morning, police said in a statement. Khulani Mathebula, aged 19, was fatally stabbed on Wednesday on his way to school. He was a grade eleven student. “The suspects were arrested in Soweto and Naturena … which brings the total number of arrested suspects to three within 24 hours,” South African Police Services spokesperson Kay Makhubela said. A 13-year-old was arrested on Wednesday, hours after the incident. (ANA)